=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Env_ex15 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 295 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 294.5134
  harmonic_decay_rate: -11.6540
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5468
  pitch_clarity: 49.7631
  inharmonicity: 0.1523
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -5.8474
  resonance_freq: 301.4648

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Env Example 15
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Env.html
// Tags: Env, Classes, envelope
// ---
// --- Example 15 ---
(
{
    var env = Env.step([0, 3, 5, 2, 7, 3, 0, 3, 4, 0], [0.5, 0.1, 0.2, 1.0, 1.5, 2, 0.2, 0.1, 0.2, 0.1]);
    var envgen = EnvGen.kr(env);
    var freq = (envgen + 60).midicps;
    SinOsc.ar(freq) * 0.1
}.play
);
